00w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ed_sheeran_foundation-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ed_sheeran_foundation-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ed_sheeran_foundation-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/ed-sheeran">埃德·希兰（Ed Sheeran）</a>已写信给英国政府的公开信，呼吁立即为音乐教育提供长期资金。</p><p>这封信由许多大牌共同签名，包括<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/elton-john">埃尔顿·约翰（Elton John）</a> ，<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/coldplay">柯尔（Coldplay）</a> ，<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/central-cee">中央中央赛（Central Cee</a> ），哈里·斯泰尔斯（ <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/harry-styles">Harry Styles），戴夫（Harry）</a> ，<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/dave">戴夫</a>（Dave），斯托姆齐<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/stormzy">（Stormzy）</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/robert-plant">罗伯特·普兰特（Robert Plant）</a> ，敦促凯尔·斯泰默（Keir Starmer）承担2.5亿英镑的音乐教育。</p><p>该倡议<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-launches-foundation-to-support-music-education-in-the-uk-music-education-has-shaped-who-i-am-3827643">于1月成立了ED Sheeran基金会后</a>，重点介绍了政府可以重点关注标准的五个领域：学校的音乐资金，音乐老师的培训，基层场所和空间的资金，音乐学徒和多样化的音乐课程。</p><p>这封信包含来自音乐界，民间社会和教育部门的数百个声音的签名，并主张政府一级的跨部门工作组，因此音乐教育不会“陷入裂缝”。 </p><figure id="attachment_3827645" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3827645" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3827645" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ed_sheeran_foundation.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ed_sheeran_foundation.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ed_sheeran_foundation-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ed_sheeran_foundation-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ed_sheeran_foundation-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ed_sheeran_foundation-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/ed_sheeran_foundation-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3827645" class="wp-caption-text"> Ed Sheeran基金会。信用：马克·沃奇</figcaption></figure><p>这封信开始说：“亲爱的凯尔·斯泰默爵士，我们正在以艺术家，公民社会和工业的身份写作，呼吁您个人对音乐的信仰以及为所有人提供机会的希望。”</p><p>它继续争辩说，音乐行业每年都会为英国经济带来76亿英镑，但说“下一代不在那里夺回ins绳”，因为许多年轻人无力学习乐器。</p><p> “去年是20多年来没有英国全球前十名单曲或榜单中的第一位，”这封信继续说道。 “The time to act is now. State schools – which educate 93% of the country&#39;s children – have seen a 21% decrease in music provision.”</p><p> “今年春天，我们共同要求提供2.5亿英镑的英国音乐教育套餐，以修复数十年的拆除音乐。音乐教育是跨部门：文化，教育，外交办公室，健康与社会护理以及商业与商业与贸易。”</p><p>它总结说：“我们知道有很多压力。” “作为艺术家，公民社会和工业，我们希望成为解决方案的一部分。”</p><p> The letter is also backed by <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/annie-lennox">Annie Lennox</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/eric-clapton">Eric Clapton</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/fred-again">Fred Again..</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/bring-me-the-horizon">Bring Me The Horizon</a> &#39;s Oliver Sykes, Richard Curtis, <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sleaford-mods">Sleaford Mods</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/snow-patrol">Snow Patrol</a> &#39;s Gary Lightbody and others.</p><p>干预措施是在本月初在<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/brit-awards">英国颁奖典礼</a>上发表的备受瞩目的演讲。 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/myles-smith-calls-on-government-support-for-music-industry-in-brits-speech-we-have-to-protect-the-foundations-3842627">Myles Smith, while accepting the Rising Star Award, said</a> : “I was a kid raised by a single mum on free school meals in a state school that only had instruments because of government-backed schemes. And I&#39;m somehow here, a four time BRIT nominee, a graduate from a Russell Group university and having the biggest hit single of 2024.”</p><p> “但是，今晚，尽管我受到了国家的关注，而这个奖项给了我这个非常酷的口语能力，但我想问三个问题。我的第一个是对政府的 - 如果英国音乐是我们拥有的最强大的文化出口之一，为什么我们将其像对待这么多年的后果一样对待？”</p><p> “How many more venues need to close, how many music programs need to be cut before we realise that we can&#39;t just celebrate success, we have to protect the foundations that make it,” he added. </p><figure id="attachment_3843212" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3843212" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3843212" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/myles-smith-brits@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Myles Smith accepting the Rising Star award on stage during The BRIT Awards 2025" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/myles-smith-brits@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/myles-smith-brits@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/myles-smith-brits@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/myles-smith-brits@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/myles-smith-brits@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/myles-smith-brits@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3843212" class="wp-caption-text">迈尔斯·史密斯（Myles Smith</figcaption></figure><p> At the same ceremony, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ezra-collective-brits-interview-community-legacy-wembley-arena-show-3843147">Ezra Collective, who won Best British Band, spoke out on the subject too</a> .他们说：“这一刻是因为伟大的青年俱乐部，伟大的老师和支持年轻人演奏音乐的伟大学校。”</p><p> Ed Sheeran基金会旨在为英国儿童提供包容性的高质量音乐教育，特别关注目前访问范围的地区。它指出，2019年BPI的一项调查发现，为弱势社区提供服务的四分之一的学校目前根本没有提供音乐课。</p><p> Last year, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-attacks-conservative-government-for-supporting-bankers-over-bands-3771292">Sheeran criticised the Conservative government for supporting bankers over bands</a> . “I&#39;ve been doing probably for the last seven years stuff with music in high schools because in my area, so basically in 2017/ 2018, my old music teacher came to me and he was like, &#39;look, the government that is currently in charge, do not value art at all, arts, drama, music.&#39; And they cut all the funding for comprehensive high schools,” he explained.</p><p> “所以我的音乐老师来找我，我认为他们必须在艺术，音乐和戏剧中分享，例如这三个主题每年700英镑。因此，我开始在当地的高中筹集资金。然后，您看到孩子们在做生产的孩子，做歌曲创作的孩子们的巨大提升，孩子们做这件事。”</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-writes-open-letter-urging-uk-government-to-invest-in-music-education-3848492">Ed Sheeran writes open letter urging UK government to invest in music education</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
